  <md:title>The Cell Cycle</md:title>
  <md:abstract>By the end of this section, you will be able to:
<list>
<item>Describe the three stages of interphase</item>
<item>Discuss the behavior of chromosomes during mitosis and how the cytoplasmic content divides during cytokinesis</item>
<item>Define the quiescent G<sub>0</sub> phase</item>
<item>Explain how the three internal control checkpoints occur at the end of G<sub>1</sub>, at the G<sub>2</sub>–M transition, and during metaphase</item>
</list></md:abstract>
